Package: g-usb-formatter
Version: 2.1.9
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.6), python3-pip, build-essential, python3-dev, libqt6core6, libqt6widgets6, libqt6gui6, libxcb-cursor0, udisks2, parted, ntfs-3g, dosfstools, e2fsprogs, pkexec, exfatprogs | exfat-utils
Maintainer: A. Serhat KILIÇOĞLU <www.github.com/shampuan>
Description: A simple and cross-platform USB disk formatting tool for Linux.
 This utility allows you to format USB flash drives using various file systems
 (NTFS, FAT32, ExFAT, Ext4) with MBR or GPT partitioning options.
 It is built with Python 3 and PySide6 (Qt).
